const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

<BaseLayout title="Epilogue — The Game of Staying Awake" description="Epilogue of The Conscious League's Rulebook">
  <article class="content">
    <header>
      <h1>Epilogue — The Game of Staying Awake</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.2em; color: var(--league-gray); margin-top: var(--spacing-md);">
        In the end, every league is made of one player: you.
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="chapter-content">
      <section>
        <h2>The Return to the Player</h2>
        
        <p>All systems eventually dissolve into the moment a human decides where to place attention.</p>
        <p>The equations fade; the dashboards dim; the algorithms hum in the background.</p>
        <p>What remains is the lived question:</p>
        
        <div style="text-align: center; margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0; padding: var(--spacing-md); background-color: #f9f9f9; border-left: 3px solid var(--league-blue); border-radius: 3px; font-style: italic;">
          Where will I spend this minute?
        </div>
        
        <p>Civilizations rise from how individuals answer that question.</p>
        <p>Awareness begins not in institutions but in perception — in the instant you choose to witness your own thought instead of react to it.</p>
        <p>That is the smallest and the hardest game in existence: the game of staying awake.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>Awareness as Practice</h2>
        
        <p>Consciousness isn't a state we reach; it's a muscle we train.</p>
        <p>Every distraction resisted, every pattern recognized, every breath noticed is a repatriation of stolen time.</p>
        <p>In a world engineered to fragment attention, staying present is an act of civil disobedience.</p>
        <p>The League teaches macro-systems to do this at scale, but the same mechanics apply internally:</p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Measure friction.</strong> Notice when attention scatters.</li>
          <li><strong>Reduce latency.</strong> Shorten the lag between seeing and understanding.</li>
          <li><strong>Return time.</strong> Use each regained moment to deepen coherence instead of chasing novelty.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>The more precisely you manage your own awareness, the less any external hypergame can use you as a pawn.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Inner League</h2>
        
        <p>Imagine every human as a self-contained League:</p>
        
        <ul>
          <li>The <strong>Pod</strong> is your mind — competing ideas learning to collaborate.</li>
          <li>The <strong>Bottega</strong> is your body — the workshop where perception meets action.</li>
          <li>The <strong>League</strong> is your community — the network that mirrors and refines you.</li>
          <li>The <strong>Index</strong> is your conscience — the inner scoreboard that tracks whether you're returning or wasting time.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>You are both player and referee.</p>
        <p>The integrity of civilization depends on the integrity of these internal leagues.</p>
        <p>When a single person becomes fully coherent, their presence reorganizes the field around them.</p>
        <p>That's how consciousness scales: not through force, but through resonance.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Rhythm of Rest</h2>
        
        <p>Staying awake doesn't mean never resting.</p>
        <p>Even awareness must exhale.</p>
        <p>Sleep, silence, art, love — these are the recovery cycles of consciousness.</p>
        <p>They keep speed from collapsing into frenzy.</p>
        <p>A civilization that measures only acceleration will burn its own mind.</p>
        <p>A conscious one will schedule stillness as infrastructure.</p>
        <p>Rest is not withdrawal from play; it is the maintenance of perception.</p>
        <p>Without rest, there is no awareness to spend.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Moral of Speed</h2>
        
        <p>We began this book with Conscious Speed: one input, infinite output.</p>
        <p>But the deeper lesson is not velocity — it's direction.</p>
        <p>Speed amplifies whatever it touches.</p>
        <p>Only consciousness ensures it amplifies wisdom instead of noise.</p>
        <p>You will be tempted, as all players are, to optimize for results.</p>
        <p>Remember: the real scoreboard is invisible.</p>
        <p>It's not what you build, but how much awareness your building returns to the field.</p>
        <p>That is the only metric that endures.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Ongoing Game</h2>
        
        <p>The Conscious Civilization will not arrive all at once.</p>
        <p>It will appear whenever a person, a team, or a city decides to align its clock with awareness.</p>
        <p>It will flicker into existence each time a system measures time honestly, or a designer chooses clarity over manipulation.</p>
        <p>You are reading this inside one of those moments.</p>
        <p>The League isn't a company or a government; it's a pattern — a way of playing that refuses to waste the future.</p>
        <p>You join it not by enrollment, but by intention.</p>
        <p>Every act of conscious creation — every simplification, every insight shared — is a move on the global board.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>The Final Move</h2>
        
        <p>When awareness pervades the field, competition dissolves into collaboration.</p>
        <p>Players stop fighting for position and start composing symphonies of motion.</p>
        <p>The game never ends, because the purpose of a conscious game is to keep creating more time to play.</p>
        <p>The victory condition is simple:</p>
        
        <div style="text-align: center; margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0; padding: var(--spacing-md); background-color: #f9f9f9; border-left: 3px solid var(--league-blue); border-radius: 3px; font-style: italic;">
          Everyone gets to stay awake a little longer.
        </div>
        
        <p>That is the legacy the Conscious League seeks to leave —</p>
        <p>a civilization that measures its greatness not in monuments or markets,</p>
        <p>but in moments of awareness multiplied across humanity.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section style="text-align: center; margin: var(--spacing-2xl) 0; padding: var(--spacing-xl); background-color: #f9f9f9; border-left: 4px solid var(--league-blue); border-radius: 5px;">
        <h2 style="color: var(--league-blue); margin-top: 0;">Fundamental Law</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.2em; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 0;">
          No human should ever waste the same time twice.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
    
    <nav class="chapter-nav" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl); padding-top: var(--spacing-lg); border-top: 1px solid #eee;">
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;">
        <a href={`${baseUrl}chapters/chapter-09`}>← Chapter 9</a>
        <a href={baseUrl}>Home →</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

